description.narrative: Progress was achieved with the Government’s first near-universal cash transfer, in response to COVID-19, with technical and financial support from UNICEF and others. Over 300,000 households received USD200, as well as information on nutrition and COVID-19 prevention, thanks to UNICEF’s advocacy for a cash-plus scheme. UNICEF supported the development and adoption of the 2021 State budget, with technical assistance to the Prime Minister’s Office and a budget brief to influence the Parliamentary debate. Further to UNICEF and UNDP advocacy and technical support, a major win was recorded on the transformative Unique ID initiative, with the Government choosing an implementation option. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
